{
  "files": [
    {
      "repo": "sg-evals/expressjs-express",
      "path": "lib/request.js"
    },
    {
      "repo": "sg-evals/expressjs-express",
      "path": "test/req.host.js"
    },
    {
      "repo": "sg-evals/expressjs-express",
      "path": "History.md"
    }
  ],
  "text": "Found 3 source files in sg-evals/expressjs-express that reference the deprecated req.host property:\n\n1. **lib/request.js (lines 452-456)**: Contains the definition of the deprecated req.host property. It is implemented as a getter using deprecate.function() that delegates to this.hostname, with the deprecation warning 'req.host: Use req.hostname instead'.\n\n2. **test/req.host.js (entire file)**: Complete test suite for req.host with 10 test cases covering basic functionality, port stripping, undefined handling, IPv6 support, and trust proxy scenarios. Tests use req.host directly at lines 12, 25, 39, 51, 64, 80, 96, 112, 128, and 145.\n\n3. **History.md (changelog)**: Contains 9 references to req.host documenting its lifecycle:\n   - Line 2726: Introduction of req.host feature\n   - Line 2552: Addition of X-Forwarded-Host support to req.host\n   - Line 2514: Fix for req.host when no Host header present\n   - Line 2368: Fix for req.host with IPv6 literals\n   - Line 1653: Fix for req.host with trust proxy hops count\n   - Line 1436: Fix for req.host with IPv6 literals\n   - Line 1286: Deprecation of req.host in favor of req.hostname\n   - Line 1284: Documentation of req.hostname as correct name for what req.host returns\n   - Line 799: Fix for req.host when using trust proxy hops count\n\nAll references are to the deprecated standalone req.host property, not req.hostname. The property is marked for removal in the next major version, as indicated by the TODO comment on line 452 of lib/request.js."
}

